## рџ§‘рџЏѕвЂЌрџЏ« what this challenge teaches u
strings in python can be distinct in 2 types: BYTES or STR
bytes has b in front
str r just strings in unicode while BYTES r raw bytes
entered_password = sys.stdin.buffer.read1() -> BYTES
bds = BYTES -> DECODE -> STRINGS
seb = STRINGS -> ENCODE -> BYTES
entered_password.decode("l1") -> STRINGS
bytes.fromhex() -> BYTES (from hex str)

